    public class UiFlexLayout.FlexCell
extends UiLayout.Cell
    A UiLayout#Cell subclass that provides additional access methods for single Flexbox layout elements.

      • grow

        public UiFlexLayout.FlexCell grow(int nGrow)
        Sets the grow factor of this cell for the Flexbox layout distribution along the flow axis. The sum of the grow factors of all cells in a layout represents the total additional layout space that is available (exceeding the minimum element sizes). The size of a cell is then determined by distributing the available space according to the ratio of it's grow factor to the sum. A factor of zero stands for the minimum size of the cell's element.
        Parameters:
        nGrow - The grow factor (a positive integer or zero)
        Returns:
        This instance for fluent invocation

      • shrink

        public UiFlexLayout.FlexCell shrink(int nShrink)
        Sets the shrink factor of this cell for the Flexbox layout distribution along the flow axis. Similar to grow(int), this will reduce the size cells with a high shrink factor more when the available layout space is reduced.
        Parameters:
        nShrink - nGrow The shrink factor (a positive, non-zero integer)
        Returns:
        This instance for fluent invocation
